derivation: a primitive root;  also as denominative from H5331 (נֶצַח)
outline:
1. to excel, be bright, be preeminent, be perpetual, be overseer, be enduring
    1. (Niphal) enduring (participle)
    2. (Piel) to act as overseer or superintendent or director or chief
kjv_def: excel, chief musician (singer), oversee(-r), set forward.
strongs_def: properly, to glitter from afar, i.e. to be eminent (as a superintendent, especially of the Temple services and its music); to be permanent
